summary: Can we just appreciate Aunt May for a minute?
body:
Can we just appreciate Aunt May for a minute?

  • This woman had to take in a child who she was not even blood related to and care for him as her own
  • She had to deal with the death of her husband at a pretty young age (I agree with MCU May- if Peter’s a teen, his aunt and uncle are hardly going to be older than his grandmother🤷🏼‍♀️)
  • She then had to raise Peter on her own and provide for everything he needed on her own
  • She then finds out that Peter is Spiderman and what does she do? She loves and supports him
  • And if you’re a comic book fan, she gets shot at the end of Civil War after Peter reveals his identity

Nothing but love and support for May Parker

summary: Living in France (or any country that isn't America, I guess) is kinda funny sometimes, because you have to wait several months...
body: Living in France (or any country that isn’t America, I guess) is kinda funny sometimes, because you have to wait several months for some American movies to be released in your country, and you get some other American movies before the Americans even do (like Avengers, for instance, which is going to be released on the 24th of April in France).
